Date: Tue, 13 Oct 2020 16:56:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/page_alloc.c: fix freeing non-compound pages
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.9.2
Git-commit: e320d3012d25b1fb5f3df4edb7bd44a1c362ec10

[ Upstream commit e320d3012d25b1fb5f3df4edb7bd44a1c362ec10 ]

Here is a very rare race which leaks memory:

Page P0 is allocated to the page cache.  Page P1 is free.

Thread A                Thread B                Thread C
find_get_entry():
xas_load() returns P0
						Removes P0 from page cache
						P0 finds its buddy P1
			alloc_pages(GFP_KERNEL, 1) returns P0
			P0 has refcount 1
page_cache_get_speculative(P0)
P0 has refcount 2
			__free_pages(P0)
			P0 has refcount 1
put_page(P0)
P1 is not freed

Fix this by freeing all the pages in __free_pages() that won't be freed
by the call to put_page().  It's usually not a good idea to split a page,
but this is a very unlikely scenario.

Fixes: e286781d5f2e ("mm: speculative page references")
